# Supabase Product Image Updater - Environment Variables
# ======================================================
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your Supabase credentials.
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit your actual .env file to version control!
#

# Your Supabase project URL
# Find it in: Supabase Dashboard > Project Settings > API > Project URL
# Example: https://xxxxxxxxxxxxx.supabase.co
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# Your Supabase service role key (NOT the anon key!)
# Find it in: Supabase Dashboard > Project Settings > API > service_role (secret)
# 
# WARNING: The service role key has FULL admin access to your database.
# - Never expose this key in client-side code
# - Never commit it to version control
# - Only use it for server-side scripts like this one
#
# Example: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

# ======================================================
# HOW TO USE
# ======================================================
#
# 1. Go to your Supabase Dashboard: https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Go to "Project Settings" (gear icon in sidebar)
# 4. Go to "API" section
# 5. Copy:
#    - Project URL → paste as SUPABASE_URL
#    - service_role key (click "Reveal" under "service_role") → paste as SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
#
# 6. Save this file as `.env` (remove .example from the name)
# 7. Run the script:
#    cd scripts
#    npm install @supabase/supabase-js dotenv
#    node update_images.js
#
# ======================================================
# IMAGE BUCKET REQUIREMENTS
# ======================================================
#
# Before running this script, make sure you have:
#
# 1. Created a storage bucket named `product-images` in Supabase
# 2. Made the bucket PUBLIC (so images can be accessed without authentication)
# 3. Uploaded the following images to the bucket:
#    - H_FireStick.png      (for Fire Stick HD)
#    - FireStick_4K.png     (for Fire Stick 4K)
#    - FireStick_4KMax.png  (for Fire Stick 4K Max)
#    - IPTV_4K_Blue.png     (for IPTV Subscription and Free Trial)
#
# To create the bucket and set it to public:
# 1. Go to Supabase Dashboard > Storage
# 2. Click "New bucket"
# 3. Name it: product-images
# 4. Check "Public bucket"
# 5. Click "Create bucket"
# 6. Upload your images
